reviews.review_text: Excellent Sounding! BEst sounding of all the excellent sources in my opinion.  Sounds like your right up front and in the sweet spot.  I think I listened to Koucky's Merriweather 85's awhile back and was impressed as well.  Great job.  REally enjoyable show as well.  I am sure loving the archive.  Having all these wonderful audience tapes to listen to keeps the music so fresh to me.  It's hard to believe this was recorded nearly 23 years ago!  And to think this was their 20 years so far year.  I can't believe its been longer than that since they played this show.  It's actually a strange sensation to me.

Great Job You for sure got the spot this night. Thank you. I was way up top with the rest of all my tour friends we smoked so much that the locals got worried and went found some security guy.Guy comes up to our section and tells us to please keep it down with the smoking your making a few worried about yourselves.No please there is no smoking at the Fox just a keep it down.Being young and dumb we followed no rules back then. We smoked well over an once of some ABSOLUTELY GREAT SMOKE..
Oh ya the show was a ton of fun also this theater had such wonderful sound did not matter where you were inside.  Also this tour was allot of fun from sunshine in Florida to snow in Rochester.
 I give this one 5 stars again and again best version here.
second best source. Very good sound here. I rank this second best behind the Senn 441 fob source. A matter of taste really. Very good performance here. Maybe second to the 11/1 show on this tour.
